        <p id="p0125">The software documentation for the MitoS and MitoA tool can be found at <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/mitosegnet" id="intref0015">https://github.com/mitosegnet</ext-link>. The MitoSegNet segmentation model, the MitoA analysis and MitoS segmentation tool (GPU/CPU) for Linux and Windows are available at <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://zenodo.org/search?page=1&amp;size=20&amp;q=mitosegnet" id="intref0020">https://zenodo.org/search?page=1&amp;size=20&amp;q=mitosegnet</ext-link>. The Python code used for generating the figures displayed in the manuscript is available at <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/MitoSegNet/MitoSegNet_AccuracyTesting_Manuscript" id="intref0025">https://github.com/MitoSegNet/MitoSegNet_AccuracyTesting_Manuscript</ext-link>.</p>
      </sec>
